Accurate for De'Lila, who only took on the appearance of Sue Storm, although she should have been given the F4 keyword or not counted against a F4 themed team. Cheap enough to play with the Ghost Rider, Hulk, Spider-Man and Wolverine of your choice. Nice to see more non-generic Skrulls being made.
March 7, 2021
tidge
From my PoV, this is the worst of the "Fantastic" Skrulls. She's tied for the lowest movement, she has the lowest damage, the 4 range is not particularly inspiring. The 2021 rules aren't doing her any favors, as there is very little reason to want to act with her instead of with other likely figures. I can't think of a trick to pull off using this figure that one of the other 30 point Skrulls wouldn't do better. The "spy" keyword isn't exactly worth it, considering what the DeepCuts Invisible Woman's 20-point line brings.

Phoenix_Icewing
Dont forget with the new willpower rules, she will be able to "leadership" herself, letting her outpace whatever target you focus on with her, and with the spy keyword, giving her access to not just skulls team, but shield, xmen, sinister syndicate, avengers initiative, and if you have Winter Soldier LE from BPI, hydra. Is she a reason to build a team? Naw. For 30 points, she can fill an excellent harasser role for the cheap with good ability to outshine her points.
